            <title>ssh ubuntu</title>
            <link>http://localhost:1313/post/ssh-ubuntu/</link>
            <pubDate>Tue, 18 Jul 2023 21:10:00 +0800</pubDate>
            <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/ssh-ubuntu/</guid>
            <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;com-autenticação-de-chave-pública&#34;&gt;Com autenticação de chave pública&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;image&#34; class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; data-flex-basis=&#34;240px&#34; data-flex-grow=&#34;100&#34; height=&#34;320&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; sizes=&#34;(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 30px), (max-width: 1023px) 700px, (max-width: 1279px) 950px, 1232px&#34; src=&#34;https://images.freeimages.com/fic/images/icons/2796/metro_uinvert_dock/320/os_ubuntu_mirror.png&#34; width=&#34;320&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A segurança de um servidor está entre as primeiras coisas que necessitamos de fazer para que as aplicações que neles utilizamos estejam assentes numa base segura.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Para tal uma medida extremamente imprtante é desablitar a autenticação por password assim como a criação de utilizador que possa administrar o servidor mas sem ser root.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Para tal vamos primeiro fazer login no nosso servidor como root.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ssh root@ip &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; servidor&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Criamos um utilizador neste caso chamado &amp;ldquo;user&amp;rdquo; com o seguite comando&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;adduser user&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;De seguida vamos conceder previlégios administrativos a este utilizador adicionando-o ao grupo &amp;ldquo;sudo&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;usermod -aG sudo user&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;A próxima etapa para proteger seu servidor é configurar a autenticação de chave pública para seu novo utilizador. A configuração aumentará a segurança do seu servidor, exigindo uma chave SSH privada para fazer o login.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Se você ainda não tiver um par de chaves SSH, que consiste em uma chave pública e uma privada, será necessário gerar uma. Se você já tem uma chave que deseja usar, pule para a etapa Copiar a chave pública.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Para gerar um novo par de chaves, digite o seguinte comando no terminal de sua máquina local (ou seja, seu computador e pressione enter.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ssh-keygen&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Com o comando anterior gerámos duas chaves criptográficas, uma chave privada e uma chave pública que vamos copiar para o nosso servidor.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Para imprimir a chave pública na máquina local é necessário executar o seguinte comando.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Selecione a chave pública e copie-a para a área de transferência.&#xA;Para habilitar o uso da chave SSH para autenticação como o novo utilizador remoto, você deve adicionar a chave pública a um arquivo especial no diretório inicial do utilizador.&#xA;No servidor e como utilizador root  digite o seguinte comando para alternar temporariamente para o utilizador antreormente criado.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;su - user&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Agora que estamos no diretório do novo utilizador criamos um diretório chamado .ssh que é um dirétorio oculto e mudamos as premissões do mesmo.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mkdir ~/.ssh&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;700&lt;/span&gt; ~/.ssh&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Agora dentro do diretório .ssh criamos um arquivo chamado &amp;ldquo;authorized_keys&amp;rdquo; com o editor de texto &amp;ldquo;nano&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;nano ~/.ssh/authorized_keys&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Salvamos o arquivo e alteramos as permições de forma a garantir a integridade do mesmo.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;600&lt;/span&gt; ~/.ssh/authorized_keys&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Depois de todas as alterações feitas voltamos ao utilizador &amp;ldquo;root&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;exit&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Precisamos de editar mais um arquivo para concluir com sucesso a nossa implementação de segurança. Utilizaremos o &amp;ldquo;nano&amp;rdquo; para isso.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Localizamos a linha que diz &amp;ldquo;PasswordAuthentication&amp;rdquo; descomentamos o símbolo #, e no final o resultado tem de ser este.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PasswordAuthentication no&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Aqui estão duas outras configurações que são importantes para autenticação apenas de chave e são definidas por padrão, mas se por algum motivo assim não for devem ficar exatamente assim.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PubkeyAuthentication yes&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ChallengeResponseAuthentication no&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Findado este processo salvamos o arquivo e reeniciamos o serviço ssh para que as mudanças possam sortir efeito.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;systemctl reload sshd&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Assim concluimos a nossa configuração inicial de segurança e passaremos apenas a usar chave ssh para nos ligarmos ao servidor que em termos de segurança é muito mais eficaz do que o método de password.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;</description>
        </item><item>
            <title>Instalação do KVM no Linux Ubuntu</title>
            <link>http://localhost:1313/post/instalar-e-configurar-o-qemu-kvm-e-o-libvirt-no-ubuntu/</link>
            <pubDate>Thu, 09 Mar 2023 21:10:00 +0800</pubDate>
            <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/instalar-e-configurar-o-qemu-kvm-e-o-libvirt-no-ubuntu/</guid>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;image&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; sizes=&#34;(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 30px), (max-width: 1023px) 700px, (max-width: 1279px) 950px, 1232px&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;instalar-e-configurar-o-qemu-kvm-e-o-libvirt-no-ubuntu&#34;&gt;Instalar e configurar o QEMU-KVM e o Libvirt no Ubuntu&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;O QEMU-KVM e o libvirt são duas ferramentas importantes para virtualização no Linux. O QEMU-KVM é uma plataforma de virtualização de código aberto que permite emular várias arquiteturas de CPU, incluindo Intel e ARM, e executar sistemas operacionais convidados em máquinas virtuais. O libvirt é uma API de gerenciamento de virtualização que fornece uma camada abstrata para interagir com diferentes hypervisors, incluindo QEMU-KVM. Juntos, eles fornecem uma solução robusta e escalável para virtualização em ambientes Linux. Neste tutorial, vamos explorar como instalar e configurar o QEMU-KVM e o libvirt no Ubuntu.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Instalação do software necessário&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt install qemu-kvm libvirt-clients libvirt-daemon-system bridge-utils libguestfs-tools genisoimage virtinst libosinfo-bin virt-manager dnsmasq&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Adicionar o utilizador aos Grupos KVM&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo adduser $USER libvirt&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo adduser $USER libvirt-qemu&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Editrar as permições de forma a usar o software com o nosso utilizador sem previlégios de root.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo addgroup &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;whoami&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; libvirt&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo addgroup &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;whoami&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; kvm&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Agora é necessário reenicar o nosso sistema operativo para que as mudanças surtam efeito.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;</description>
        </item><item>
            <title>Instalação do Wireguard num servidor Ubuntu</title>
            <link>http://localhost:1313/post/wireguard-no-ubuntu/</link>
            <pubDate>Mon, 27 Feb 2023 20:10:00 +0800</pubDate>
            <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/wireguard-no-ubuntu/</guid>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;image&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; sizes=&#34;(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 30px), (max-width: 1023px) 700px, (max-width: 1279px) 950px, 1232px&#34; src=&#34;https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/98/Logo_of_WireGuard.svg&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;este-artigo-trata-da-criação-de-uma-vpn-com-o-protocolo-wireguard&#34;&gt;Este artigo trata da criação de uma VPN com o protocolo Wireguard.&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Para tal é necessário tem um servidor neste caso iremos utilizar um servidor Ubuntu.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Para facilitar a instalação vamos utilizar um script que automatiza todo o processo. Esse scipt está disponivél no Github e todos os créditos vão para o seu desenvolvedor.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Todo este processo em vai ter lugar no nosso servidor em primeiro lugar e logo em seguida configuramos o cliente.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Em primeiro lugar clonamos o script, alteramos as permições e executamos o mesmo.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;curl -O https://raw.githubusercontent.com/angristan/wireguard-install/master/wireguard-install.sh&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod +x wireguard-install.sh&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;./wireguard-install.sh&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;No final de executados os comandos a cima é só seguir os passos que são bastante intuitivos. No final é gerado um QR code com toda a informação necessária para configurar o cliente.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;cofiguração-do-cliente&#34;&gt;Cofiguração do cliente&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Neste caso vamos utilizar o Linux Ubuntu como cliente mas estes passos podem ser facilmente replicados em qualquer distribuição Linux.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt install wireguard &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;De seguida criamos um arquivo de texto com o editor &amp;ldquo;nano&amp;rdquo; e inserimos a informação obtida através do QR code.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo nano /etc/wireguard/wg0.conf &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Fica aqui um exemplo de como fica o arquivo no final de inserir as informações geradas.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;Interface&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PrivateKey &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; ICkL1OUeq2UOXd9FLlgHxOesvsN+WXxb8/BrNBgSllg&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Address &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; 10.66.66.2/32,fd42:42:42::2/128&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;DNS &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; 94.140.14.14,94.140.15.15&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;Peer&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PublicKey &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; 8o7MZzWVM4jBkcJYSFpbBEdd7bLhWDCOwXMr0K7vVCQ&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PresharedKey &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; fTO+tOawy912esxEW1zNYrcgLpYvuIqj17UPI+GOyb0&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Endpoint &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; 139.162.208.222:65513&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;AllowedIPs &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; 0.0.0.0/0,::/0&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Salvamos o aquivo de texto e só nos resta establecer a ligação ao nosso servidor VPN. Para iniciar o serviço basta executar o seguinte comando na nossa máquina cliente.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo wg-quick up wg0&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Para a ligação VPN começar na inicialização do sistema o comando é o seguinte.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo systemctl enable wg-quick@wg0&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;E voilá temos o nosso próprio servidor VPN de maneira bastante simples.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;</description>
        </item></channel>
